but the sine function is 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

 at all multiples of 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

, hence the equation above becomes 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\pi}{2}=0$
\end_inset

.
