\]

\end_inset

Now, again plugging in 
\begin_inset Formula $x=\pi$
\end_inset

, we obtain
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{2} & =\cos\pi-\cos2\pi+\cos3\pi-\dots\\
 & =1-(-1)+1-(-1)+\dots\\
 & =\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}1
\end{align*}

\end_inset

